<h3 id='field-find_tiles'>Field : find_tiles()</h3><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight lua tab-lua"><code><span class="kd">local</span> <span class="k">function</span> <span class="nf">search_function</span><span class="p">(</span> <span class="n">tile</span> <span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">tile</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">get_team</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">Team</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">Blue</span>
<span class="k">end</span>

<span class="kd">local</span> <span class="n">tile_list</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">field</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">find_tiles</span><span class="p">(</span> <span class="n">search_function</span> <span class="p">)</span>
</code></pre></div>
<blockquote>
<p>The above snippet finds all the <strong>Tiles</strong> that are currently owned by the <strong>Blue Team</strong>.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>This function iterates through all of the s on the battlefield, and returns a list of them that matches a specific criteria <em>(provided by a function)</em>.</p>
<h4 id='function-call'>Function Call</h4>
<p><code>field:find_tiles( search_function )</code></p>
<h4 id='return-value'>Return Value</h4>
<p><strong><code>vector</code></strong></p>
<h4 id='parameters'>Parameters</h4>
<p><strong><code>function</code></strong> <code>search_function</code><br>
    &emsp;<em>A function that filters the s you <strong>want</strong> to include.</em><br></p>
<div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight lua tab-lua"><code><span class="kd">local</span> <span class="k">function</span> <span class="nf">search_function</span><span class="p">(</span> <span class="n">tile</span> <span class="p">)</span>
  <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">tile</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="n">get_team</span><span class="p">()</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">Team</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">Red</span>
<span class="k">end</span>
</code></pre></div>
<aside class="notice"><code>search_function</code> requires <b>one</b>  parameter and to return a <b><code>boolean</code></b>.<br>
Any  that causes the function to return <code>true</code> will be added to the list.</aside>
